content: In my junior high school, my teacher taught me renju and shogi.
I had kept studying renju until 1981, then I stopped.
Sorry, shogi is a kind of Japanese borad game.
When I entered university, I was too lazy and had lots of spare time.
So I started renju again(from 1984). At that time, I studied and analyzed everyday.
I could join Meijinsen from 1986 and win 1987 for the first time.
I am lazy too but still no free time......
After that, I lost against Nakamura 3 times.
Finally, I beat Nakamura in 1994 and became Meijin for the first time.
And I became World Champion in 1995, you know.
The title of today's lesson is "Nakamura's Mind".
Nakamura is a great player. He got Meijin title 22 times and WC twice.

Nakamura is a great player. He got Meijin title 22 times and WC twice.
I believe Nakamura is the most wonderful player. He made a renju history.
It is very good for you to learn Nakamura's mind.
First, we will learn black move.
Nakamura sometimes attack for black wonderfully.
He said basically renju is based on black.(same as Ando?)
He found new tactics of I5. Next 7th move is famous.
Please write down next move all of you just after I say "Go".
K7 would be withe win, it is said.
here is a few smart student
This is a typical Nakamura's move. What do you think of next move?
This problem is difficult a little bit. So I give you 60 seconds.
He thinks attacking or limit move of opponent attacking.
E7 is correct. I must explain a little more.
IF black stone put on D10, D8 or..., Black has VCF.
So white is not able to protect...
Nakamura knows Keima opening very well.
After 30 minutes, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move.
He moved J8 but I think K8 is also correct.
14 was bad. Now 14 -F11is better probably you know.
Next problem is protection. Where is 33th move?
After 30 seconds, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move
k12 is correct. I don't mean his move is best. I can say you learn his mind.
Actually, K12 or J11 is a good point.
First of all, from D12. Of course 23 is VCF.
So white must play perfectly protection.
After 30 seconds, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move
L10 is correct. This move must be famous.
IF 25 is this, where 26? please say "me"
You are sure white could stop.
However, black can win from this.
After 30 seconds,, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move
M9 is correct. It was easy for you.
Next is I11 again. It is said 14th move is impossible before.
After 30 seconds, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move
After Nakamura found a new white protection, black could not win.
20-d6 seems to transfer to variant of 19-d9
It must be more difficult. so go ahead.
why c6 is best - it is Naka's move :)

Next is from I12. Until 23 is winning position.
24th move is complicating move and has a terrible tactics.
After 60 seconds,, I will say Go. Please predict and write down next move
J9 is correct. I must explain.
Nakamura found 24th move when he understand 30th move!
do you know, Mr Kawamura, after this 24?
Of course black can win. Anyone?
Probably you understood Nakamura was great.
That's all for today's theme. Nakamura's mind.
Could I tell you Nakamura's mind?
I sm soglad to hear it.
